{"id":"279587916_Robust_Design_via_Generalized_Linear_Models","abstract":"A single data transformation may fail to satisfy all the required properties necessary for an analysis. With generalized linear models (GLMs), the identification of the mean-variance relationship and the choice of the scale on which the effects are to be measured can be done separately, overcoming the shortcomings of the data-transformation approach. GLMs also provide an extension of the response surface approach. In this paper, we set out the current status of the GLM approach to the analysis of data from quality-improvement experiments and discuss its merits.","authors":["Youngjo Lee","John A. Nelder"],"meta":["January 2003Journal of Quality Technology 35(1):2-12","DOI:10.1080/00224065.2003.11980187"],"references":["266415690_A_Comparison_Between_Maximum_Likelihood_and_Generalized_Least_Squares_in_a_Heteroscedastic_Linear_Model","262292546_Signal-to-Noise_Ratios_Performance_Criteria_and_Transformations","323330024_Generalized_Linear_Models_for_Quality-Improvement_Experiments","318774972_Joint_Modeling_of_Mean_and_Dispersion","317599012_Generalized_Linear_Models","314735141_Understanding_Industrial_Designed_Experiments","313064337_Taguchi's_parameter_design_A_panel_discussion","313061658_Performance_measures_independent_of_adjustment_with_discussion","310332444_Modelling_and_analysing_correlated_non-normal_data","308087511_Response_Surface_Methodology","287488389_Generalized_Linear_Models_and_Process_Variation","287389446_Generalized_Linear_Models","284531776_Empirical_Model-Building_and_Response_Surfaces","277664929_Generalized_Linear_Models_Monographs_on_Statistics_and_Applied_Probability_No_37","270443298_Joint_Modeling_of_Mean_and_Dispersion","266301843_Modelling_Variation_in_Industrial_Experiments","264919958_Hierarchical_generalised_linear_models_A_synthesis_of_generalised_linear_models_random-effect_models_and_structured_dispersions","264254563_Generalized_linear_models_for_quality-imp